    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p>Fire beetles are large, territorial insects the size of a wolf, their chitinous shells glowing with deep amber and crimson bioluminescence. They hunt in loosely coordinated packs, using their crushing mandibles to seize and immobilize prey before dragging it back to their nest burrows. The glands running along their abdomens can ignite under duress, releasing a burst of searing biological fire.</p>",
